## cumulative analysis

Aggregating the data progressively over time.
Helps to understand whether our business is growing or declining.
âˆ‘ [cumulative Measure] By [Date Dimension]
Running Total Sales By Year
moving Average Cost By Month

-- wrong concept
    SELECT 
    DATETRUNC(MONTH, order_date) AS order_date,
    SUM(sales_amount) AS total_sales
    --SUM(sales_amount) OVER(ORDER BY DATETRUNC(MONTH, order_date)) AS running_total
    FROM gold.fact_sales
    WHERE order_date IS NOT NULL
    GROUP BY DATETRUNC(MONTH, order_date)
    ORDER BY DATETRUNC(MONTH, order_date)

Expplaination: we can not use directly WINDOWW function inside a single query, ned to use in outer query
